# data['Arrival Time'] = data['Arrival Time'].astype('datetime64')
data['Arrival Time'] = pd.to_datetime(data['Arrival Time'], dayfirst=True)
data['year'] = pd.DatetimeIndex(data['Arrival Time']).year
data['month'] = pd.DatetimeIndex(data['Arrival Time']).month
grouped_data_by_date = data.groupby(["Area Name", "year", "month"]).agg({'In Violation?': np.mean}).reset_index()
print("Group data to calculate the average violations by month in each year")

In [10]:
# Set plot dimensions and subplot number
sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(20,64)})
fig, ax = plt.subplots(8,3)

# Loop and plot
count = 0
for j in range(8):
    for i in range(3):
        if count < 23:
            small_data = grouped_data_by_date.loc[(grouped_data_by_date['Area Name'] == data['Area Name'].unique()[count])]
            small_data_index_fix = small_data.reset_index(drop=True)
            small_data_index_fix['index'] = small_data_index_fix.index
            sns.regplot(x="index", y="In Violation?", data=small_data_index_fix, ax=ax[j, i]).set_title(data['Area Name'].unique()[count])
            count += 1

#Display plot
fig.delaxes(ax[7, 2])
fig.tight_layout()
plt.show()

# sns.set(rc={'figure.figsize':(20,64)})
# fig, ax = plt.subplots(8,3)
plt.figure(figsize=(20,20))
sns.scatterplot(x="Side Of Street", y="In Violation?", data=sorted_side_parking_data, s=100)
sns.lineplot(x="Side Of Street", y="In Violation?", data=sorted_side_parking_data)
sns.regplot(x="Side Of Street", y="In Violation?", data=sorted_side_parking_data)
for line in range(0,sorted_side_parking_data.shape[0]):
    label = "(" + str(round(sorted_side_parking_data["Side Of Street"][line], 3)) + ", " + str(round(sorted_side_parking_data["In Violation?"][line], 3)) + ")"
    plt.text(sorted_side_parking_data["Side Of Street"][line]+0.01, sorted_side_parking_data["In Violation?"][line], 
             label, horizontalalignment='left', size='medium', color='black', weight='semibold')

plt.show()
